1. Create a Java file named DatabaseGUI.java

2. Type the Java program and save it

3. Install MySQL Server

sudo apt update
sudo apt install mysql-server

4. Start MySQL Service

sudo systemctl start mysql

5. Open MySQL

sudo mysql

6. Create Database

CREATE DATABASE studentdb;

7. Use Database

USE studentdb;

8. Create Table

CREATE TABLE student(
    id INT,
    name VARCHAR(50)
);

9. Exit MySQL

exit;

10. Download MySQL JDBC Driver

11. Extract ZIP file

12. Copy:
mysql-connector-j-9.7.0.jar

into same folder where DatabaseGUI.java is present

13. Open Terminal in Project Folder

14. Compile Program

javac -cp ".:mysql-connector-j-9.7.0.jar" DatabaseGUI.java

15. Run Program

java -cp ".:mysql-connector-j-9.7.0.jar" DatabaseGUI

16. GUI Window will open

17. Enter:
Student ID
Student Name

18. Click Insert Button

19. Message:
Record Inserted Successfully

20. Check Records

sudo mysql

USE studentdb;

SELECT * FROM student;
